HEADWORD: Cross-springer
<hw>Cross"-spring`er</hw> <pr>(-spr?ng`?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>One of the ribs in a groined arch, springing
from the corners in a diagonal direction. <note>[See <xex>Illustr</xex>.
of <er>Groined vault</er>.]</note></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

